SUMMARY:India at the Inflection Point
DESCRIPTION:Geopolitical realignments. Technological disruptions. The mounting urgency of the climate crisis.  \nAs the world undergoes multiple\, simultaneous transformations\, India is faced with charting its own course. \nRajiv Kumar\, Kamal Bali\, Manish Sabharwal\, Nitin Pai\, and Mohandas Pai bring together perspectives from policy\, industry\, and innovation to examine what it will take to navigate this era of uncertainty. As India navigates frontier technologies like AI\, strengthening strategic autonomy\, addressing climate imperatives and fostering inclusive growth\, the choices are critical. \nHow can we become a developed nation in the coming decades? \nIn collaboration with: \n \n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/india-at-the-inflection-point/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Books,Development,Governance,International Relations,Nonfiction,Policy & Regulation
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Thumbnail-30.jpg
END:VEVENT
