SUMMARY:Three Colours
DESCRIPTION:Three of the six Hindustani gharanas\, each with its own preferred repertoire of raags\, taals\, compositions and improvisation techniques. \nThis evening\, Mukul Kulkarni moves through each tradition. Before every item\, he names the stylistic sources of what he is presenting\, illuminating the differences between traditions. He is accompanied by Sagar Bharatraj on tabla and Niranjan ‘Bharat’ Hegde on harmonium. A performance built around a superbly trained artiste\, deeply exploring raags\, going somewhere that no one\, not even he\, can predict. \nOne unhurried evening. Immersion and imagination.  \nSupported by:\n \n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/three-colours/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Music,Performing Arts
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Thumbnail-31.jpg
END:VEVENT
